After the war, Joshua returned to[N]
Jehanna and reclaimed his birthright[N]
as the nation's king, although he ruled[N]
with the same carefree attitude that[N]
had defined his wandering years. Rather[N]
than fully committing to the life of a[N]
monarch, Joshua allowed himself frequent[N]
trips across the continent. During which[N]
he kept in touch with a grumbly rouge who[N]
had reinvigorated his love for gambling[N]
and adventure.[X]
